pineapple you texted me about.

495
00:23:28.490 --> 00:23:31.330
I'm realizing right at this
moment you meant on a pizza.

496
00:23:32.250 --> 00:23:34.646
That's okay. We can maybe
have a pool house luau.

497
00:23:34.670 --> 00:23:36.130
How does that sound?

498
00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:38.750
Look. it's time I told you.

499
00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:41.130
I found a bigger place.

500
00:23:42.300 --> 00:23:43.300
And I'm moving out.

501
00:23:44.130 --> 00:23:45.130
That's awesome. Sean.

502
00:23:45.720 --> 00:23:47.640
That's great. When are
you… when are you moving?

503
00:23:48.970 --> 00:23:49.970
Three days ago.

504
00:23:51.010 --> 00:23:52.956
Everything happened super fast.

505
00:23:52.980 --> 00:23:55.166
Derek has this awesome place.

506
00:23:55.190 --> 00:23:57.326
and he needs someone
to fix it up for him.

507
00:23:57.350 --> 00:24:00.310
And you know how much I like
helping out well-to-do white dudes.

508
00:24:01.020 --> 00:24:02.560
We are an overlooked demographic.

509
00:24:03.860 --> 00:24:05.046
I should have told you sooner

510
00:24:05.070 --> 00:24:08.796
but with Alice leaving. and.
hell. now everyone leaving.

511
00:24:08.820 --> 00:24:10.240
- I just...
- hey. Sean.

512
00:24:11.200 --> 00:24:12.660
There's no need to apologize. man.

513
00:24:14.540 --> 00:24:15.636
Look. when you moved in here.

514
00:24:15.660 --> 00:24:18.106
it was never with the intention
that you were going to stay forever.

515
00:24:18.130 --> 00:24:19.130
Yeah.

516
00:24:20.170 --> 00:24:21.750
I'm really happy for you.

517
00:24:23.130 --> 00:24:24.380
Come on.

518
00:24:25.220 --> 00:24:26.390
What can I say?

519
00:24:27.380 --> 00:24:28.550
I'm really gonna miss you.

520
00:24:29.680 --> 00:24:31.080
I'm gonna be like four blocks away.

521
00:24:31.760 --> 00:24:33.720
Way to ruin the moment. Sean.

522
00:24:37.640 --> 00:24:40.390
I'm betting Marisol's waiting for
you at your new place right now.

523
00:24:41.020 --> 00:24:42.400
She might be.

524
00:24:43.940 --> 00:24:45.610
Fuck the game. Get out of here.

525
00:24:52.200 --> 00:24:54.910
- Keys to the pool house.
- Yes. Thanks.

526
00:24:57.540 --> 00:24:58.710
Thank you. Jimmy.

527
00:24:59.790 --> 00:25:00.880
For everything.

528
00:25:21.440 --> 00:25:24.796
We're so happy you two
decided to make a pit stop.

529
00:25:24.820 --> 00:25:29.466
Yeah. we talked it out. and we picked
this over microdosing at a Red Sox game.

530
00:25:29.490 --> 00:25:31.530
These people still have
access to my father.

531
00:25:32.240 --> 00:25:33.386
Speak of the devil.

532
00:25:33.410 --> 00:25:35.636
Anyway. how could I
pass up an opportunity

533
00:25:35.660 --> 00:25:37.766
for probably my last home
cooked meal in a while?

534
00:25:37.790 --> 00:25:39.936
Don't sleep on college dining halls.

535
00:25:39.960 --> 00:25:43.266
I used to eat cereal with
vanilla soft serve instead of milk.

536
00:25:43.290 --> 00:25:45.920
Maybe take a little
weed gummy right before.

537
00:25:46.760 --> 00:25:48.100
I'm on one right now.

538
00:25:48.720 --> 00:25:50.906
Was dad just texting you
to see if I got here okay?

539
00:25:50.930 --> 00:25:52.470
Yeah. he also said.

540
00:25:52.970 --> 00:25:57.680
"Sean's moving out. happy for
him. but also kind of sad. you know?"

541
00:25:58.600 --> 00:26:01.286
- What did you write back?
- Thumbs-up emoji.

542
00:26:01.310 --> 00:26:03.666
- Dude.
- Why is that thumb black?

543
00:26:03.690 --> 00:26:05.956
Gaby did it. I-I don't know
how to change it back.

544
00:26:05.980 --> 00:26:09.190
He told you that he was sad
and that is how you responded?

545
00:26:09.780 --> 00:26:11.836
Don't you know how
alone he is right now?

546
00:26:11.860 --> 00:26:14.256
No. he's not. He's got that
girl that's too cute for him

547
00:26:14.280 --> 00:26:15.870
but when she speaks. you get it.

548
00:26:16.450 --> 00:26:18.096
- He doesn't have her anymore.
- What?

549
00:26:18.120 --> 00:26:19.426
When did that happen?

550
00:26:19.450 --> 00:26:21.436
A few weeks ago. I told you.

551
00:26:21.460 --> 00:26:23.226
Do you not listen to me?

552
00:26:23.250 --> 00:26:25.290
It depends. You guys say so much stuff.

553
00:26:25.840 --> 00:26:27.026
I have to filter.

554
00:26:27.050 --> 00:26:28.736
- Dad.
- What is wrong with you?

555
00:26:28.760 --> 00:26:30.696
My god. You are unbelievable.

556
00:26:30.720 --> 00:26:32.656
What do you want me to do?

557
00:26:32.680 --> 00:26:35.776
Maybe just give him
some fatherly advice.

558
00:26:35.800 --> 00:26:37.010
Jesus Christ.

559
00:26:37.720 --> 00:26:39.826
I'm not his father.

560
00:26:39.850 --> 00:26:43.786
If you are my honorary
grandpa. doesn't that make you…

561
00:26:43.810 --> 00:26:45.206
Papa pimp.

562
00:26:45.230 --> 00:26:48.706
Look. I'm 3.000 miles away.

563
00:26:48.730 --> 00:26:50.730
Even if I had a magic bullet.

564
00:26:51.450 --> 00:26:55.500
Jimmy has still got to learn how
to figure out this shit for himself.

565
00:26:57.780 --> 00:27:00.676
To hell with a home cooked
meal. Let's get a pizza.

566
00:27:00.700 --> 00:27:01.806
That's a great idea.

567
00:27:01.830 --> 00:27:03.186
Bring the gummies.

568
00:27:03.210 --> 00:27:05.146
Yeah. that'll be good.

569
00:27:05.170 --> 00:27:06.460
You're not invited.

570
00:27:07.920 --> 00:27:09.000
Thank god.

571
00:27:37.570 --> 00:27:40.016
- I'm Batman.
- Wow.

572
00:27:40.040 --> 00:27:43.250
Hey. Hey. Dan. How
you… how you doing?

573
00:27:43.790 --> 00:27:44.790
It's…

574
00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:47.686
It's pretty quiet around here?

575
00:27:47.710 --> 00:27:49.840
Yeah. look's like everybody's gone.

576
00:27:51.760 --> 00:27:54.816
Which means we can either
do our session in my office.

577
00:27:54.840 --> 00:27:57.986
or we can gather up
all the couch cushions

578
00:27:58.010 --> 00:28:00.140
and do it in a fort.

579
00:28:01.220 --> 00:28:02.220
Office. please.

580
00:28:02.810 --> 00:28:03.850
Your loss. Dan.

581
00:28:04.730 --> 00:28:07.900
And Stan and his wife
are moving to Paris.

582
00:28:08.440 --> 00:28:09.820
Can you believe that?

583
00:28:11.110 --> 00:28:12.626
Who wants to live in fucking Paris?

584
00:28:12.650 --> 00:28:13.940
I think most people. Dan.

585
00:28:15.740 --> 00:28:18.256
Hey. you said you were gonna
get yourself back on the dating apps.

586
00:28:18.280 --> 00:28:19.926
Did you make a profile yet?

587
00:28:19.950 --> 00:28:23.766
No. but I did give Siri
an Australian accent.

588
00:28:23.790 --> 00:28:26.080
It's kind of a vibe.

589
00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:28.580
- Dan.
- I know.

590
00:28:29.790 --> 00:28:32.396
After three years of therapy.
I'm back where I started.

591
00:28:32.420 --> 00:28:33.646
Not true.

592
00:28:33.670 --> 00:28:36.316
You have come so far
over the past few years.

593
00:28:36.340 --> 00:28:37.680
Do not forget that.

594
00:28:38.510 --> 00:28:39.970
Look. everybody has setbacks.

595
00:28:40.800 --> 00:28:46.060
If I'm honest. I still find myself
right back to feeling alone.

596
00:28:47.940 --> 00:28:49.956
Like everybody's moving forward but me.

597
00:28:49.980 --> 00:28:51.020
Yeah.

598
00:28:51.610 --> 00:28:53.900
So. maybe we both agree
to keep working on that.

599
00:28:56.110 --> 00:28:57.200
But in the meantime.

600
00:28:57.990 --> 00:29:00.620
maybe we can try to find
some positives in the solitude.

601
00:29:01.830 --> 00:29:04.846
When you wake up
tomorrow. remind yourself.

602
00:29:04.870 --> 00:29:08.250
alone doesn't always
have to mean lonely.

603
00:29:21.890 --> 00:29:23.680
What the fuck are you
doing here. Matthew?

604
00:29:25.520 --> 00:29:27.206
I'm house-sitting while
my folks are out of town.

605
00:29:27.230 --> 00:29:29.496
and my mom said I could
swing by when I got hungry.

606
00:29:29.520 --> 00:29:30.690
Well. you can't.

607
00:29:32.770 --> 00:29:34.440
Just grab a pizza and get out of here.

608
00:29:35.860 --> 00:29:37.240
I love pepperoni.

609
00:29:38.780 --> 00:29:42.046
Hey. Do you wanna.
like. have a cup of coffee?

610
00:29:42.070 --> 00:29:43.716
We could eat that pizza.

611
00:29:43.740 --> 00:29:46.846
Just… I don't know. we
could just hang out and talk.

612
00:29:46.870 --> 00:29:48.476
I'm good. Thanks.

613
00:29:48.500 --> 00:29:49.880
No. me too. I'm good too.

614
00:30:08.890 --> 00:30:10.246
Hey. Paul.

615
00:30:10.270 --> 00:30:12.166
Hey. what's up?

616
00:30:12.190 --> 00:30:14.876
You know me. man. I
just finished working out.

617
00:30:14.900 --> 00:30:16.706
Getting ready to attack the day.

618
00:30:16.730 --> 00:30:19.626
You're alone in your underwear
doing nothing. aren't you?

619
00:30:19.650 --> 00:30:21.426
Very much so. yes.

620
00:30:21.450 --> 00:30:23.740
Okay. well. I just called because

621
00:30:25.080 --> 00:30:28.000
we really should have that
bye-bye breakfast sometime.

622
00:30:29.000 --> 00:30:31.436
Yeah. I would… I would
love that. man. When?

623
00:30:31.460 --> 00:30:32.710
How's now?

624
00:30:38.590 --> 00:30:39.970
Hi… - hey.

625
00:30:40.840 --> 00:30:41.920
Paul.

626
00:30:43.680 --> 00:30:46.240
What are you doing here? How
long… how long are you in town for?

627
00:30:46.810 --> 00:30:48.866
- Just a couple of hours.
- That's insane.

628
00:30:48.890 --> 00:30:50.326
What if I had plans this morning?

629
00:30:50.350 --> 00:30:51.730
You didn't.

630
00:30:52.980 --> 00:30:55.520
- Paul.
- Let me talk. okay?

631
00:30:59.070 --> 00:31:01.176
Life threw you a curveball

632
00:31:01.200 --> 00:31:03.756
so. to try and control things.

633
00:31:03.780 --> 00:31:07.030
you picture how you want
them to go in your own head and…

634
00:31:08.910 --> 00:31:10.200
That doesn't work.

635
00:31:10.750 --> 00:31:14.346
If you can't let go of this shit on your own

636
00:31:14.370 --> 00:31:15.500
then I have to…

637
00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:18.130
I have to keep trying
to shake it out of you.

638
00:31:18.960 --> 00:31:20.186
You hear what I'm saying?

639
00:31:20.210 --> 00:31:23.816
I… yeah. I do. but can we just
talk about this over waffles?

640
00:31:23.840 --> 00:31:26.196
No. you're not eating with me.

641
00:31:26.220 --> 00:31:27.220
You're eating with her.

642
00:31:29.680 --> 00:31:33.616
Hi. Can I get a cappuccino please?

643
00:31:33.640 --> 00:31:35.430
- Yeah. no problem.
- Thank you so much.

644
00:31:37.730 --> 00:31:39.690
Not how you pictured it?

645
00:31:40.280 --> 00:31:41.756
You fucking jimmied me.

646
00:31:41.780 --> 00:31:44.200
That's right. I fucking jimmied you.

647
00:31:45.200 --> 00:31:47.160
Look. kid. if you're ever
going to move forward.

648
00:31:47.740 --> 00:31:49.700
you've got to let go of the past.

649
00:31:50.290 --> 00:31:51.630
And I know that's scary.

650
00:31:52.960 --> 00:31:53.960
But you're…

651
00:31:54.460 --> 00:31:55.880
You're never gonna forget Tia.

652
00:31:57.170 --> 00:31:59.090
Hell. you're never going to forget me.

653
00:32:00.000 --> 00:32:01.000
No one will.

654
00:32:02.880 --> 00:32:07.220
Letting go of the past just
means you don't allow…

655
00:32:08.260 --> 00:32:11.430
Your scars to hold you back anymore.

656
00:32:12.270 --> 00:32:13.706
I'm covered in them. Paul.

657
00:32:13.730 --> 00:32:14.730
Good.

658
00:32:15.940 --> 00:32:21.110
What a shame to be 42 years of age
and not completely covered in scars.

659
00:32:22.190 --> 00:32:26.440
They're the evidence of a life fully lived.

660
00:32:27.660 --> 00:32:28.870
I don't want this.

661
00:32:31.450 --> 00:32:34.306
I don't want you to have to fly
all across the fucking country

662
00:32:34.330 --> 00:32:35.960
just to make sure that I'm okay.

663
00:32:37.620 --> 00:32:40.040
- I don't want to be a burden to you.
- You're not.

664
00:32:42.090 --> 00:32:43.590
You're more of a son to me.

665
00:32:44.210 --> 00:32:46.340
I don't know why I never said that before.

666
00:32:47.720 --> 00:32:48.970
I think you're strong.

667
00:32:50.010 --> 00:32:51.300
I think you don't need me.

668
00:32:52.510 --> 00:32:53.826
But for as long as I'm around.

669
00:32:53.850 --> 00:32:57.850
if you think you need
me. I will be there for you.

670
00:32:58.650 --> 00:32:59.940
Because I love you.

671
00:33:01.570 --> 00:33:02.626
- Okay?
- Okay.

672
00:33:02.650 --> 00:33:03.850
Now. you got a choice to make.

673
00:33:05.280 --> 00:33:11.530
Either stay stuck. or you
can go make some new scars.

674
00:33:13.240 --> 00:33:15.200
I got a fucking airplane to catch.

675
00:33:18.620 --> 00:33:19.870
Choose wisely.

676
00:33:48.990 --> 00:33:50.740
- Hi.
- Hi.
